### Branch Strategy

**Recommended Branch Structure**:

```
main (or master)
  └── before-net11-upgrade (tag)
      └── upgrade/dotnet-11.0 (branch)
          └── net11-upgrade-complete (tag)
```

**Workflow**:
1. Work on `upgrade/dotnet-11.0` branch
2. Test thoroughly
3. When validated, merge to `main`:
   ```bash
   git checkout main
   git merge upgrade/dotnet-11.0 --no-ff -m "Merge .NET 11.0 upgrade"
   ```
4. Keep `upgrade/dotnet-11.0` branch for reference (don't delete immediately)

**Rollback Options**:
- **Full rollback**: `git checkout main && git reset --hard before-net11-upgrade`
- **Partial rollback**: Cherry-pick commits, revert specific changes

